- What even is that?

7
00:00:28,737 --> 00:00:30,405
What even is that?

8
00:00:30,489 --> 00:00:31,823
What's all that?

9
00:00:31,907 --> 00:00:33,742
-What the…
-What is this?

10
00:00:33,825 --> 00:00:35,827
What the… What am I to do?

11
00:00:35,911 --> 00:00:38,872
This is the fate for you to read.

12
00:00:38,956 --> 00:00:40,207
What is this?

13
00:00:40,290 --> 00:00:41,583
What? Feet?

14
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:43,085
Feet? What the heck?

15
00:00:45,796 --> 00:00:47,339
Is this for real?

16
00:00:47,422 --> 00:00:49,091
Why are we looking at people's feet?

17
00:00:49,675 --> 00:00:50,926
What the…

18
00:00:51,009 --> 00:00:52,469
What's with all these feet?

19
00:00:52,552 --> 00:00:54,346
What's going on?

20
00:00:54,429 --> 00:00:55,597
Oh, geez…

21
00:00:56,223 --> 00:00:57,516
I can't believe this.

22
00:00:58,100 --> 00:00:59,184
What are we to guess?

23
00:00:59,268 --> 00:01:03,355
On the screen are 9 pairs of feet.

24
00:01:03,855 --> 00:01:06,692
Identify the feet
that belong to a homeless person.

25
00:01:07,442 --> 00:01:10,028
- Ah…
- This is just…

26
00:01:10,529 --> 00:01:13,407
Nine pairs of feet? Oh, what…

27
00:01:14,366 --> 00:01:18,412
I was flabbergasted
by the 9 pairs of feet.

28
00:01:18,495 --> 00:01:20,038
SHAMAN JUNGHWA
8-YEAR SHAMAN

29
00:01:20,122 --> 00:01:23,834
As many as 9 pairs?
You people are unbelievable.

30
00:01:23,917 --> 00:01:26,169
How did they even photograph those feet?

31
00:01:26,253 --> 00:01:28,130
They're all different ages.

32
00:01:30,173 --> 00:01:31,550
I've never done this.

33
00:01:31,633 --> 00:01:33,427
- Feet…
- Feet?

34
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:35,387
This will be tough.

35
00:01:35,470 --> 00:01:38,015
I found it so fascinating.

36
00:01:38,098 --> 00:01:39,766
Do you know this "utterly shocked" meme?

37
00:01:39,850 --> 00:01:43,186
This is exactly how I felt, for real.

38
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:45,063
HONG YULJAE
6-YEAR SHAMAN

39
00:01:46,690 --> 00:01:50,068
A shaman usually
doesn't read feet.

40
00:01:50,152 --> 00:01:53,905
As for me, I don't let people
enter my shrine with bare feet.

41
00:01:53,989 --> 00:01:56,700
But they're asking me to read fortunes
based on people's feet.

42
00:01:57,451 --> 00:01:58,702
I was so lost.

43
00:01:59,202 --> 00:02:01,580
I don't know.
I just have to do it. There's no choice.

44
00:02:02,247 --> 00:02:03,665
Just staring at the feet won't help.

45
00:02:03,749 --> 00:02:04,791
YOUNG MASTER MINT
3-YEAR SHAMAN

46
00:02:09,296 --> 00:02:11,298
YOUNG MASTER BYEON
15-YEAR SHAMAN

47
00:02:11,381 --> 00:02:13,967
Please tell me if this person is homeless.

48
00:02:14,051 --> 00:02:15,719
I must find the homeless person, Granny.

49
00:02:15,802 --> 00:02:18,680
Heavenly Fairy, Child spirits,
find the homeless.

50
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:22,434
I'd never done anything like that.

51
00:02:22,517 --> 00:02:25,604
I used my fan and bells
and even tried rice divination.

52
00:02:27,564 --> 00:02:29,274
I also used my crystal balls.

53
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:33,528
I tried absolutely everything I could

54
00:02:33,612 --> 00:02:35,656
to figure out the answer.

55
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,533
CHEONHAE HWASIN
2-YEAR SHAMAN

56
00:02:39,701 --> 00:02:41,620
October 1993.

57
00:02:41,703 --> 00:02:43,664
Born in 1977… 1990…

58
00:02:43,747 --> 00:02:46,583
Born in 1991… 1982… 1985…

59
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:50,504
They were born on lunar October 18, 1990.

60
00:02:50,587 --> 00:02:53,256
I had to read
many people's fortunes at once.

61
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:54,633
Nine people, was it?

62
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:59,429
It felt like my head would explode.
I had to read so many at once.

63
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:03,058
Honestly, it was too much
to handle at once.

64
00:03:03,558 --> 00:03:06,019
I never take notes while reading fortunes,

65
00:03:06,103 --> 00:03:10,607
but this time I had to, for all 9 of them.

66
00:03:14,528 --> 00:03:16,279
I didn't expect to see feet.

67
00:03:16,363 --> 00:03:18,615
It wasn't just 4 or 5 pairs.

68
00:03:18,699 --> 00:03:20,242
There were a whopping 9.

69
00:03:20,826 --> 00:03:22,202
Then one moment…

70
00:03:22,285 --> 00:03:25,539
A homeless person.
Someone who sleeps on the street.

71
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:29,668
I had an idea of what card
to find. So I laid out all 9 cards.

72
00:03:29,751 --> 00:03:31,420
And when I turned them over,

73
00:03:31,503 --> 00:03:33,588
only 1 person got a different card.

74
00:03:34,673 --> 00:03:36,425
It meant they're the homeless person.

75
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:42,222
This should be easy-peasy
for Mr. Kim Baekmun, right?

76
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:44,433
- Yes, he's a foot reader.
- The foot reader?

77
00:03:44,516 --> 00:03:45,559
KIM BAEKMUN
35-YEAR FOOT READER

78
00:03:45,642 --> 00:03:47,477
This could be his chance to shine.

79
00:03:48,311 --> 00:03:50,689
We got a foot reading question.

80
00:03:50,772 --> 00:03:51,815
"This one's for me."

81
00:03:52,816 --> 00:03:54,484
I was determined to get it right.

82
00:03:55,986 --> 00:03:58,613
What do you look for when reading feet?

83
00:03:59,448 --> 00:04:00,490
All right.

84
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:01,741
When you're reading feet,

85
00:04:01,825 --> 00:04:04,786
you look at the top, the soles,

86
00:04:04,870 --> 00:04:08,165
the color of the feet, overall shape,

87
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:10,917
and even the lines on the soles.
Basically everything.

88
00:04:11,001 --> 00:04:15,714
Everyone's toes and toenails
are different in shape and size.

89
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:18,800
To see someone's financial fortune,
you compare lines on both soles.

90
00:04:18,884 --> 00:04:22,846
Also, the fourth toe
shows your financial fortune.

91
00:04:22,929 --> 00:04:24,931
This. It's looking nice.

92
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:26,641
Very good.

93
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:30,645
Six… Feet number four?

94
00:04:34,524 --> 00:04:36,526
It's probably this one.

95
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:40,947
TAEUL LEE DOKYU
11-YEAR FACE READER

96
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:43,784
I don't know much about foot reading,

97
00:04:43,867 --> 00:04:46,036
but I was still quite confident.

98
00:04:47,954 --> 00:04:50,457
I studied podiatry.

99
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:55,545
And it's a medical field that focuses
on one's health aspects.

100
00:04:55,629 --> 00:04:59,007
It looks at the shape, arch,
and structure of the feet.

101
00:04:59,090 --> 00:05:03,386
Foot reading, on the other hand,
is about reading one's fate.

102
00:05:04,763 --> 00:05:09,351
Podiatry focuses on health aspects through
the nerves and shape of one's feet.

103
00:05:10,769 --> 00:05:15,148
I realized 1 particular pair stood out
during my podiatric examinations.

104
00:05:15,941 --> 00:05:18,652
I'd never seen feet like that
in my studies.

105
00:05:19,903 --> 00:05:23,156
They had the worst shape, were calloused,

106
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:26,660
and had what looked like tetanus scars.

107
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:30,080
I thought, "This is the one.
The homeless person."

108
00:05:32,415 --> 00:05:33,416
Let's have a go.

109
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:41,132
Thirty-sixFate Readers are up
for the challenge.

110
00:05:41,216 --> 00:05:42,217
Whoa!

111
00:05:42,801 --> 00:05:44,553
This is a lot more than I expected.

112
00:05:44,636 --> 00:05:45,637
Ah…

113
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:49,099
Here are the Fate Readers
who will present their readings.

114
00:05:51,059 --> 00:05:52,143
HONG YULJAE
6-YEAR SHAMAN

115
00:05:52,227 --> 00:05:53,395
MONAD
8-YEAR TAROT MASTER

116
00:05:53,478 --> 00:05:54,646
Oh!

117
00:05:54,729 --> 00:05:55,730
KIM BAEKMUN
35-YEAR FOOT READER

118
00:05:55,814 --> 00:05:57,357
- Mr. Kim made it.
- He's in.

119
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:58,608
- Oh, good.
- He's in.

120
00:06:00,902 --> 00:06:02,571
TAEUL LEE DOKYU
11-YEAR FACE READER

121
00:06:02,654 --> 00:06:03,697
I'll get this right.

122
00:06:04,447 --> 00:06:05,866
I really can't tell from the feet.

123
00:06:06,616 --> 00:06:09,703
The first to press the button,
Hong Yuljae.

124
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:11,329
- Hong Yul…
- Yuljae.

125
00:06:11,413 --> 00:06:13,039
He studied Fine Arts at Hongik University.

126
00:06:14,457 --> 00:06:19,754
I'm Hong Yuljae of Hwawol Shrine,
and I'm based in Hwaseong.

127
00:06:19,838 --> 00:06:22,799
I studied fashion design
at Hongik University College of Fine Arts.

128
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:28,221
One of the deities I serve is

129
00:06:28,305 --> 00:06:31,266
a grandfather that used to be a painter.

130
00:06:31,349 --> 00:06:34,936
So when I read fortunes,
he shows me the situation as a painting,

131
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:37,480
like the works
of Shin Yunbok or Kim Hongdo.

132
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:41,109
I interpret details of the painting
and explain them to the client.

133
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:44,321
And in my case,
when I am touched by a deity,

134
00:06:44,404 --> 00:06:47,157
I feel a sensation of heat.

135
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:49,993
There were 9 pairs of feet,

136
00:06:50,076 --> 00:06:53,038
so I put my hand on each of them
to see if I could feel the heat.

137
00:06:54,581 --> 00:06:58,585
There was one that felt so hot
when I touched it.

138
00:06:59,294 --> 00:07:01,630
So I figured it was my deities
trying to tell me the answer.

139
00:07:02,589 --> 00:07:04,674
That heat gave me certainty.

140
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:09,179
The birth chart
of the fourth person.

141
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:11,556
They're meant to have
great fortune and wealth,

142
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:14,517
but if they lose such luck, they lose big.

143
00:07:14,601 --> 00:07:15,977
So I thought

144
00:07:16,061 --> 00:07:17,937
this person was most likely homeless.

145
00:07:18,563 --> 00:07:19,564
He's right.

146
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:23,109
It seems
they're in a precarious state right now,

147
00:07:23,943 --> 00:07:26,780
and having a homeless' birth chart
doesn't mean they're meant to be a beggar.

148
00:07:27,364 --> 00:07:31,076
So sometimes their birth chart
could give off a good vibe.

149
00:07:31,159 --> 00:07:32,661
- Oh…
- Mmm.

150
00:07:32,744 --> 00:07:35,038
Oh, a homeless's birth chartisn't
the same as thatof a beggar.

151
00:07:35,789 --> 00:07:38,083
So, based on my reading,

152
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:40,960
I think number 4 is the homeless person.

153
00:07:41,044 --> 00:07:42,212
He's good.

154
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:44,673
He's right. We have a winner.

155
00:07:44,756 --> 00:07:48,718
-His reading is always similar to mine.
-Him?

156
00:07:48,802 --> 00:07:51,096
Next, Kim Baekmun.

157
00:07:51,179 --> 00:07:52,347
Ah…

158
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:54,015
The foot reader.

159
00:07:54,099 --> 00:07:56,434
I'm excited. Foot reading.

160
00:07:56,518 --> 00:07:57,894
Number 4.

161
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:02,399
I'd say number 4 is the most likely.

162
00:08:02,482 --> 00:08:07,153
The reason is,
we all have lines on our feet.

163
00:08:07,237 --> 00:08:10,990
There are some basic ones everyone has,

164
00:08:11,074 --> 00:08:13,076
but they're almost invisible
on these feet.

165
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:14,869
He's right.

166
00:08:15,704 --> 00:08:16,871
There are no lines.

167
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:21,292
Having no lines means

168
00:08:21,376 --> 00:08:24,462
